titre: Por qué no me tocó ser Michael Keaton?
synopsis: A guy who is at home and speaks alone...
A short amateur film made by G.D Stami which deals with ambiguities of  one's  ill-fated life.

In Kermit the Frog's own word's, "Hands down this is the best short film of the year and hits so close to home." Love Comes to Koozebane follows a socially anxious Kooze floating into the abyss of unpredictability. Will love come to Koozebane?

Forced to travel with her boyfriend to a horror festival, Laine begins to experience disturbing visions associated with the urban legend of The Creeper. As the festival arrives and the blood-soaked entertainment builds to a frenzy, she becomes the center of it while something unearthly has been summoned.
